**Day 5 — Permissions & Privileges**

## 📌 Overview
On Day 5, I practised Linux file permissions, user management, and privilege control. These are critical for securing systems and preventing unauthorised access.

---

## 🛠 Commands Used

### 🔐 Check File Permissions
```bash
ls -l test.txt
✏️ Change Permissions (chmod)
chmod 600 test.txt
Owner: Read & Write
Others: No access
👤 Create New User
sudo useradd -m testuser
🔑 Set Password
sudo passwd testuser
🔄 Switch User
su - testuser
🚫 Permission Test
cat /home/.../test.txt

👉 Result: Permission Denied

👑 Use sudo (Admin Privileges)
sudo ls /root
🔄 Change Ownership (chown)
sudo chown root:root test.txt
